result.name: Levain Bakery x Coco Espresso

reviews.text:
Their pastries are marvelous!
The all day breakfast size are larger than expected, which was nice.
Not much seats here, quite cosy.

Good coffee and always friendly! But I wish you don’t charge that 12$ when redeeming loyalty card, for somebody that gets the same thing every day. After all your pricing is on the high side to begin with.

Levain Bakery x Coco Espresso has a branch on Tai Wong West in the Wanchai district. This is an interesting concept shop and coop between one of the better coffee shop franchises (Coco Espresso) and a good local bakeries (Levain). Opening hours are 8am to 8pm (weekdays) and 9am to 6pm (weekends). 

We had breakfast here recently and were very happy with the white coffees served as well as the delicious Camember, ham, apple and raspberry jam on sourdough break. This was a surprisingly good dish, made with fresh and tasty ingredients. Plan on returning soon for a reorder and to try other items on their breakfast menu.

Decor is urban industrial with clean walls and just a few tables. Staff are friendly and prepare coffee drinks and foods in a timely manner. 

Overall, a nice first visit to the Levain Bakery x Coco Espresso concept shop in Wanchai. This is a good addition to the morning food scene in this area of the city. Looking forward to a return visit.

I like Coco’s coffee. I like theses guys bread. But sandwiches are not their forte. Smoked salmon still with freezer ice, forgotten sandwiches, all takes ages, and they don’t seem to have an idea what they are doing in the kitchen. Better stick to coffee and baked goods.
Great coffee, yummy bread but the set breakfast is a bit pricey, it would be better if they could offer bread basket or just toast as breakfast option
